==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piperidine
<hw>Pi*per"i*dine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An oily liquid alkaloid, <chform>C5H11N</chform>, having a hot,
peppery, ammoniacal odor. It is related to pyridine, and is obtained by
the decomposition of piperine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piperine</ent>⟦br⟧
